claim: After 30 October 2018 , See You Again reported 3.8 billion views on YouTube .
truth: As of November 1 , 2018 , the video has received over 3.8 billion views on YouTube making it the third most viewed video on the website .

claim: More than 6,165 positive coronavirus cases had been registered in China by January 29 , 2020 .
truth: As of January 29 , 2020 , approximately 6,171 cases have been confirmed including in every province of China .

claim: There were under 337,000 cases of COVID-19 before March 23 , 2020 .
truth: As of 23 March , more than 337,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,600 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: More than 14,550 people have died of COVID-19 as of March 22 , 2020 .
truth: As of 22 March , more than 334,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,600 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: More than 83 % of COVID-19 deaths were in patients aged 70 or older before April 2 .
truth: As of April 2 , 130 of 154 ( 84 % ) COVID-19 deaths were in patients aged 70 or older , and no one younger than 50 was known to have died from the disease in Massachusetts .

claim: More than 285,000 COVID-19 cases came to light from over 180 countries and territories by March 21 , 2020 .
truth: As of 21 March , more than 286,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 180 countries and territories , resulting in more than 11,800 deaths and 93,000 recoveries .

claim: The severe acute respiratory syndrome had more than 8,300 cases and more than 800 deaths between November 2002 and July 2003 .
truth: Between November 2002 and July 2003 , an outbreak of SARS in southern China caused an eventual 8,422 cases , resulting in 916 deaths reported in 37 countries , ? ua=1 with the majority of cases in China ( 9.6 % fatality rate ) according to the World Health Organization ( WHO ) .

claim: In early April 2020 , the impact of the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic on sports caused the regular season for Women 's NBA to be postponed .
truth: On 3 April , the Women 's National Basketball Association ( WNBA ) announced that they will postponed the start of training camp and regular season which was originally scheduled for 15 May . The 2020 WNBA draft was held virtually and televised on 17 April 2020 without players , guests , and media on-site.

claim: There had been less than 375,000 confirmed cases of COVID-19 worldwide by March 23 .
truth: As of 24 March , more than 378,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 16,400 deaths and over 101,000 recoveries .

claim: After August 30 , 2018 , See You Again reported 3.7 billion views on YouTube .
truth: As of September 1 , 2018 , the video has received over 3.7 billion views on YouTube making it the third most viewed video on the website .

claim: China had less than 6,165 coronavirus cases before January 30 , 2020 .
truth: As of January 29 , 2020 , approximately 6,162 cases have been confirmed including in every province of China .

claim: Before May 2019 , the main T-Series channel had uploaded more than 13 thousand videos .
truth: The main T-Series channel primarily contains Indian music videos ( Bollywood music and Indi-pop ) as well as Bollywood film trailers , and uploads several videos every day , and has uploaded 13.3 thousand videos as of 21 April 2019 .

claim: The motion picture Traffic was released in 2000 and features a fight between the Juárez Cartel and the Tijuana Cartel .
truth: Some US sources estimate the cartel 's income reached as high as $ 200 million a week under former boss Amado Carrillo Fuentes , who mysteriously died in July 1997.A look inside a giant drug cartel , Christian Science Monitor , 1999 The Juárez Cartel was featured battling the rival Tijuana Cartel in the 2000 motion picture Traffic .

claim: The single `` Sober '' peaked at number 122 in the charts .
truth: It was sent to contemporary hit radio on May 3 , 2016 . `` Sober '' was set to be released as the fifth single from Revival if the era kept going but never happened , it peaked at number 122 in the |Billboardbubbling100| chart.

claim: Resident Evil 5 sold less units than Capcom 's Street Fighter II with less than 14.30 million copies .
truth: As of December 2018 , when taking into consideration the sales of all versions and re-releases of titles , Resident Evil 5 was the third best-selling Capcom game overall , behind and Monster Hunter : World ( 11.9 million ) and Street Fighter II ( 14 million ) .
